content:
Creating an HTML page with a navigation bar and a footer is a great way to start building a website. Below is a simple example to get you started. This example uses basic HTML and CSS for styling. You can customize it further according to your needs.

### HTML

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Web Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <nav class="navbar">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="content">
        <h1>Welcome to Our Website</h1>
        <p>This is a simple web page example with a navigation bar and a footer.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2023 Your Company. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
```

### CSS (styles.css)

```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.navbar {
    background-color: #333;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.navbar ul {
    list-style-type: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.navbar li {
    float: left;
}

.navbar li a {
    display: block;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.navbar li a:hover {
    background-color: #575757;
}

.content {
    padding: 20px;
}

.footer {
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 10px 0;
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 100%;
}
```

### Explanation:

1. **HTML Structure**: 
   - The HTML file contains a basic structure with a navigation bar (`<nav>`), main content (`<div class="content">`), and a footer (`<footer>`).
   - The navigation bar is a simple unordered list of links.
   - Main content is where you can add more details about your website.
   - The footer is placed at the bottom of the page.

2. **CSS Styling**:
   - The CSS file defines styles for the body, navigation bar, content, and footer.
   - The navigation bar is styled with a dark background and white text. The links change background color on hover.
   - The footer is fixed at the bottom of the page and has a similar style to the navigation bar.

Feel free to expand and modify this template to suit your specific requirements.
